103
00:08:14,607 --> 00:08:16,678
- Go, Angel.
- Yeah, I'm psyched.

104
00:08:18,628 --> 00:08:21,698
<i>Yeah, me too.
I'm about to be published.</i>

105
00:08:23,127 --> 00:08:25,615
<i>I sent that manifesto to the Tribune.</i>

106
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:29,207
<i>Guess I've been taking some cues
from Lila lately,</i>

107
00:08:29,228 --> 00:08:30,878
<i>and not just in bed.</i>

108
00:08:31,327 --> 00:08:34,249
<i>I'm tired of reacting
to the moves of agent Lundy</i>

109
00:08:34,284 --> 00:08:35,678
<i>and his super posse.</i>

110
00:08:36,428 --> 00:08:39,278
<i>Time to control their actions
for a change.</i>

111
00:09:02,228 --> 00:09:05,443
Betsy Court, 16.
Blunt-force beating.

112
00:09:05,927 --> 00:09:09,003
Looks like she was sunning herself
and never saw it coming.

113
00:09:09,020 --> 00:09:10,610
Who called in the body ?

114
00:09:10,914 --> 00:09:14,185
Craig Wilson, the stepfather.
He's right over there.

115
00:09:18,527 --> 00:09:20,347
Wilson told the reporting officer

116
00:09:20,382 --> 00:09:23,278
that he came home for lunch
and found her that way.

117
00:09:24,459 --> 00:09:26,745
You and Dexter resolve your issues ?

118
00:09:26,780 --> 00:09:29,839
As far as I'm concerned. Why ?
The bitch come crying to you again ?

119
00:09:30,311 --> 00:09:33,202
There's blood work to be done,
and if you can't control yourself,

120
00:09:33,237 --> 00:09:35,093
I need to call in
another detective.

121
00:09:35,128 --> 00:09:37,293
I won't say anything to hurt
the girl's feelings.

122
00:09:37,328 --> 00:09:40,508
- Goddamn it, I'm not joking.
- Do I look like I'm laughing ?

123
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:45,055
- I wish you would. You used to.
- Bullshit. I never laughed.

124
00:09:46,126 --> 00:09:47,947
Yeah, you're probably right.

125
00:09:49,027 --> 00:09:53,588
I'm not gonna try to scare you anymore.
Reality is you're out of free passes.

126
00:09:53,623 --> 00:09:56,455
I already stopped Dexter from filing
a complaint against you once.

127
00:09:56,517 --> 00:09:59,041
- I never asked you to do that.
- I did it,

128
00:09:59,103 --> 00:10:02,085
out of my own concern
over your obsessive behavior.

129
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:05,004
I'm on the line,
so if you bully Dexter in any way,

130
00:10:05,039 --> 00:10:08,450
if you even look at him wrong,
I won't be responsible for the fallout.

131
00:10:08,485 --> 00:10:10,511
- You got it ?
- I got it.

132
00:10:11,727 --> 00:10:14,825
- You're backing the fucking freaktard.
- James.

133
00:10:25,827 --> 00:10:27,445
Where you been, Dexter ?

134
00:10:29,027 --> 00:10:30,698
You don't bring me doughnuts.

135
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:32,708
You don't sing me love songs.

136
00:10:32,862 --> 00:10:34,555
How are you, Camilla ?

137
00:10:36,527 --> 00:10:37,913
I've been better.

138
00:10:38,834 --> 00:10:40,912
Well, that doesn't sound good.

139
00:10:45,527 --> 00:10:48,466
Sergeant Doakes dropped by
my file room yesterday.

140
00:10:48,727 --> 00:10:52,778
He requested the case files
for the 1973 shipping-yard murders.

141
00:10:53,347 --> 00:10:56,708
I gave him the same line I gave you
when you came sniffing around,

142
00:10:56,712 --> 00:11:00,350
said all that old stuff was boxed up
in the basement of city hall.

143
00:11:00,828 --> 00:11:02,778
That made him real angry.

144
00:11:04,707 --> 00:11:06,203
He scared me, Dexter.

145
00:11:07,428 --> 00:11:10,078
That's not right.
He shouldn't do that.

146
00:11:11,765 --> 00:11:16,200
I always assumed your father asked me
to destroy those files to protect you.

147
00:11:17,528 --> 00:11:18,555
Now...

148
00:11:18,975 --> 00:11:20,972
I'm not sure what's going on.

149
00:11:21,227 --> 00:11:23,788
- Camilla...
- Now, I don't want to know.

150
00:11:23,823 --> 00:11:25,628
I just don't want to get fired.

151
00:11:26,927 --> 00:11:29,623
I'm retiring next year.
Did I tell you ?

152
00:11:29,627 --> 00:11:32,551
I've been looking forward
to staying home with Gene.

153
00:11:32,937 --> 00:11:36,008
You won't lose your retirement.
I won't let that happen.

154
00:11:36,043 --> 00:11:39,856
I can stall Sergeant Doakes
for a few days,

155
00:11:40,057 --> 00:11:44,053
but eventually, he'll figure out
the file's missing, just like you did.

156
00:11:44,088 --> 00:11:46,857
And he'll track it back to me,
just like you did.

157
00:11:47,128 --> 00:11:48,734
I'll take care of this.

158
00:11:48,974 --> 00:11:50,487
You have my word.

159
00:11:57,084 --> 00:11:59,162
<i>So much for threatening Doakes.</i>

160
00:11:59,197 --> 00:12:03,588
<i>He won't back off till he exposes
the twisted branches of my family tree,</i>

161
00:12:03,623 --> 00:12:06,888
<i>from my father's indiscretions
to my murderous brother</i>

162
00:12:06,923 --> 00:12:08,852
<i>to the root of all evil...</i>

163
00:12:09,343 --> 00:12:10,543
<i>me.</i>

164
00:12:27,027 --> 00:12:30,002
<i>- Why aren't you at the Tribune ?
- What for ?</i>

165
00:12:30,527 --> 00:12:33,339
Our guy's not gonna leave
dna evidence on a document.

166
00:12:33,364 --> 00:12:34,944
But the thrill of the hunt.

167
00:12:34,979 --> 00:12:37,741
I've had that particular thrill.
I'll leave it to younger men.

168
00:12:38,165 --> 00:12:39,365
Besides,

169
00:12:39,650 --> 00:12:42,029
it's easier for me
to do my part from here.

170
00:12:42,064 --> 00:12:43,792
